Memorandum: > YouTube Poop check-point -- YTP content will be enforced in this sector; to be precise, YTP secks jokes will be prohibited from any actual explicit or overly-detailed content in this sector;
YTPs may be as weird as necessary, so long as content sin does not form (i.e. no more "Blue f@#%s his aunt" type YTPs);
YTP secks jokes are prohibited from transgressing the NC-17 joke line (therefore, no discernible nudity, no sensical intercourse, no sentence mixing to describe anything beyond the NC-17 line);
webcancer content will no longer be permitted in this sector (therefore, no more of certain yiff image rips, no more cancer rips such as shotah rips, in-character shots cannot be personally-aimed or actually offensive).


I am debating either revamping old YTPs to comply with the new YTP safe-content requirements, or just trashing old YTPs altogether.


All new YTPs will abide by these restrictions, created for the sake of the YTP community's health in this sector. Content can only improve; abiding by these new rules should be a nonissue; after all, how long can "YTP: Blue f@#%s his aunt" possibly be actually enjoyable by a forum-level community? (And at the very least, not draw flak?)
